reviewText: I was in middle school during the Kennedy presidency. That was a very innocent time for our country. I wanted to add it to my collection.
Very good. I can't get enough of Jackie.
I found it a bit boring, but historically interesting. Quite slow at times and repetitive. As usual, a glimpse into our American past and how beloved one President was to the country and the world.

Fast service on quality dvd showing development of kennedy life and legend. Enjoyable to see once again.

This brief but interesting look at one of the most documented families in the world. Stockard Channing does a great job in her narration and some of the film and photos are some that I have not seen before.  It documents the mystic and the media facination with the family accuratly and with a bit more dignity than so many others.  Well worth the purchase
